\subsection{Thermal Buffering}
Heat transfer through the thermal buffer is governed by Fourier’s law:
\begin{equation}
  Q = -k_A \nabla T,
\end{equation}
where \(Q\) is the heat flux, \(k_A\) is the thermal conductivity of the buffering material, and \(\nabla T\) denotes the temperature gradient. Active cooling elements are controlled via PID loops:
